<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09129b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09129b">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09129b"> 129(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abelites, marry &mdash; f <font color="green">[&amp;]</font> adopt / foster</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">ABEL: The Abelians, or Abelites, a sect in northern Africa mentioned by St. Augustine &hellip; pretended that they imitated Abel by marrying, yet condemned the use of marriage. They adopted children who also married and lived in the same manner as their foster-parents. <small> <a name="TCE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TCE1"><cite title="source">Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) I, 36a</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03146b" href="c03all.htm#c03146b">VI.C.03:146(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
